definition.value: A purine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside having guanine as the nucleobase.
A heparan sulfate composed of a backbone of repeating alpha-L-iduronosyl-(1->4)-N-sulfonyl-alpha-D-glucosamine units joined by (1->4)-linkages.
An epoxydodecadienamide isolated from several species, including Acremonium, Acrocylindrum and Helicoceras. It inhibits the biosynthesis of several lipids by interfering with enzyme function.
